The Zondo Commission will hear Aviation related evidence. JOHANNESBURG - The Zondo Commission of inquiry will on Monday, hear more aviation-related testimony.
Former SAA board member and SAA Technical chairperson, YakheÂ Kwinana, is expected to testify. Kwinana was accused earlier this year of having asked for kickbacks. Director of S-R-S Aviation, Sibongile Sambo, told the commission Kwinana wanted a 100-million rand kickback from a US company to influence a tender process. Kwinana has denied the allegations.